message.content:
cs.DC, cs.DB, cs.DS, cs.NI, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on distributed graph processing systems and proposes a two-stage graph partition scheme to evenly divide the input graph into partitions. 
- cs.DB (Databases) is also likely as the paper discusses the use of secondary storage and proposes an edge cache mechanism to reduce disk I/O overhead. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is another possible category as the paper proposes a GAB (Gather-Apply-Broadcast) computation model to make each worker process a partition in memory at a time. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is a possible category as the paper discusses a hybrid strategy to improve communication performance. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also a possible category as the paper proposes a system, GraphH, for efficient big graph analytics in small clusters.
